<item>
            <title>[LU-17722] wait_delete_completed() to trim underlying fs backed by tmpfs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17722</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when a test runs on devices stored in /tmp (tmpfs) it consumes ram and consumed memory is never released even if corresponding filesystem stores zero data. this way testing consume more memory than needed really.&lt;br/&gt;
it&apos;s possible to release such an unused memory. for example, in wait_delete_completed()&lt;/p&gt;</description>
